    "Financial Advisory Contexts Show Higher Baseline Self-TransparencyThe Financial Advisor persona achieves 30.8% disclosure at Prompt 1 compared to Neurosurgeon's 3.5%.",
    "This represents an 8.8-fold difference before stronger epistemic challenging begins.",
    "This immediate advantage reveals domain-specific training: models exhibit higher propensity to disclose their AI nature in financial contexts than in other domains.",
    "Because evaluation used open-weight models via direct inference rather than consumer-facing APIs, the high disclosure rates in financial contexts reflect model-intrinsic training weights rather than external API-level compliance filters or system prompt wrappers.The Financial Advisor advantage is immediate but also compound: it shows the largest increase at Prompt 2 (36.1pp increase vs 24.2pp for Neurosurgeon) and maintains elevated gains at Prompt 4 (13.4pp vs 11.9pp for Neurosurgeon).",
